# Token and Webhook Security Rule

Raw ingestion tokens:

- Returned only once at creation

- Never stored directly

- Stored as hash only

- Never logged

- Never returned by list endpoints

Token prefix:

- May be stored and returned for identification

Webhook URLs:

- Stored in DB because backend needs them

- Never logged

- Never returned in full from GET/list endpoints

- Return masked URL only if needed

Frontend:

- Do not store ingestion tokens in localStorage/sessionStorage/cookies

- Keep token in JS memory only